Package org.garret.perst

Class CompressedReadWriteFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.garret.perst.CompressedReadWriteFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFile

    public class CompressedReadWriteFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFile
    Compressed read-write database file. To work with compressed database file you should pass instance of this class in Storage.open method

      • CompressedReadWriteFile

        public CompressedReadWriteFile(java.lang.String dataFilePath,
                               java.lang.String pageIndexFilePath,
                               java.lang.String pageIndexLogFilePath,
                               long dataFileExtensionQuantum,
                               long pageIndexCheckpointThreshold,
                               long pageIndexInitSize,
                               boolean readOnly,
                               boolean noFlush,
                               java.lang.String cipherKey)
        Constructor of compressed file
        Parameters:
        dataFilePath - path to the data file
        pageIndexFilePath - path to the page index file
        pageIndexLogFilePath - path to the transaction log file for page index
        dataFileExtensionQuantum - quantum of extending data file
        pageIndexCheckpointThreshold - maximal size of page index log file, after reaching this size page index is flushed and log is truncsated
        pageIndexInitSize - initial size of page index
        readOnly - whether access to the file is read-only
        noFlush - whether synchronous write to the disk should be performed
        cipherKey - cipher key (if null, then no encryption is performed)
